## --- terminate/break the terminal
> ctr + c

## --- go to Home
> F11

## --- CUT + PASTE in Mac
> First, COMMAND + C (this copies the file)
> Then, go to the final destination and type 'COMMAND + OPT (alt) + V'

## --- Ctrl + Alt + Del (in windows)
> command + opt (alt) + escape (in Mac)

## How to backup your mac using Time Machine?
> Open Time Machin from Mac System Preference (top left)
> Then, put it ON
> Then, go to the external drive. Right click & select back up now.


## How to open Sublime Text from Mac Command Line:
        * sudo ln -s /Applications/Sublime\ Text.app/Contents/SharedSupport
       /bin/subl /usr/bin/subl

## To navigate in Finder: 
        > shift + cmd + g

## clear screen
        > cmd + k
        
        
## [Sat 02Apr2016]. How to combine multiple png files.
   > Select all the files and open.
   > Go to View -> Sidebar -> Collapse All.





